Description: Foot of pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine light red-brown. Oval stamps with chariot and animal symbols.
Curator's comments: A very curious piece. The stamps are presumably jeux d'esprit. See Johnston, 'FRagmenta Britannica V' Bulletin of the Institute of Classical Studies 59 (2016) 51-2. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0072)
